<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-496-812  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 496 812.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 25 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hacker gets jail term. (Kevin Mitnick)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer hackersComputer CrimesCourt Cases.andO;Person:    Mitnick, Kevin (cases).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>HACKER GETS JAIL TERM LOS ANGELES, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1989 JUL 18 (NB) --Kevin Mitnick, the computer hacker convicted of using stolen MCI accessnumbers to tap into computers and copy valuable programs has been sentencedto a year in jail and six months rehabilitation.andP;  US District Judge MarianaPfaelzer issued the prison sentence after she learned Mitnick could not beplaced in a hospital- operated therapy program because federal sentences mustbe served in federal facilities and the program was not under federalgovernment contract.andP;  Expert witnesses had testified that Mitnick suffersfrom an impulse disorder and used illegal computer activities to boost hisself-esteem.andP;  After serving his prison term (five more months in the prisonfacility and six months at a federally run halfway house), Mitnick willremain under conditional release for three years.andP;  He will be forbidden topossess any illegal or unauthorized access to computers or telecommunicationsequipment and will not be allowed to associate with known computer hackers.andO;Mitnick will be allowed to own a personal computer.andP;  (JanetEndrijonas/19890721)</TEXT></DOC>